message: It's been agreed upon in the talk section already before this edit war begun that this paragraph was to be removed from this article.  Take it to the talk section if you wish to keep the paragraph.  It has already been agreed upon by several people that the source does not state what the sentence says it does.  This is a violation of sentences needing to be verifiable and must be removed.
again source does NOT state that Trumps team said widespread fraud.  Stop lying about what your source says
/* GSA Administrator Emily W. Murphy letter to Joe Biden */

Nowhere in your source (source number 12 that is cited) does Trump or anyone in Trumps campaign ever say that widespread voter fraud occurred.  Your article states that is what he says, even though the source you have added does not say that.  I removed that sentence from the article until it is written properly.
/* Again with conspiracy theory */ new section

Removed opinion from the article and left it with just with what the article should say.  Removed "without evidence" from the Trump claims of voter fraud as that is misleading because there has been evidence presented, and to say that there was none is misleading and not true, and goes away from the nature of this specific topic.
This sentence was removed per the agreement in the talk section that the source was not verifiable with the information in the article.
It's not for us to decide when sources are right or wrong. If the source says "without evidence", so do we. Otherwise please take this to the talk page
/* removing the ongoing protest material from the article */
/* Biased or inaccurate article promoting one side of a debate still in litigation. Language needs to be "cleaned up". */ reflist-talk

BRD. The removal of the main articles doesn't make sense. The linking is appropriate because of the identicality of the subject matter between the main articles and the sub-sections, and topic scope of the sub-sections. Removed corresponding link in the see also page. Debate on the talk page first if you want to restore it
